19:32  29 March 2008

Ever dreamed of killing someone with a flashbang or a smokegrenade? 
Well, here's your chance in this nice map! with textures from multiple famous maps.
Take a flashbang or smokegrenade out of the weapon dispencer or at the spawn, and throw it
to your enemy. Get one point for each kill. 
There's a timer wich counts to 60 (1 minute...) and after that everyone's that. so: no stupid campers
or stuff. They won't survive. 
I hope it's going to be succesfull, have fun!

Ivar van Wooning
Ingame: i3D.!\/4R


(note/tip: You spawn with 1 HP, a Flashbang or Smokegrenade does 1 Damage and can so kill you in one trow.)

(note/tip: You can add bots ingame with the bot_add_ct or bot_add_t command. Then you have funny, but easy enemy.)

Remake of fy_flashlighttag.  More on the way.  Map is dark so its a must that you use your flashlight in order to navigate the map (thats what gives it its name).  Night vistion helps a little too so you can pick up other peoples flashlights better.  The only reason there are lights on the map are, so you can tell what spawn you are at so you dont keep going around and around.

This is my first map I have made for CS:S.  

It is a simple map that is small and maze like.

The bottom floor is coverd with a waist high water level and hides smoke grenades randomely strewen about the map.  Also the bottom floor is more of a mase and has meny dead ends the might hide a few wepon stashes here and there.  The top floor is almost the same but you can get lost a lot quicker on the top the on the bottom.  All the walls allow you to shoot though them.

The entier map is dark save for where you spwan thous giveing the map its name.

Max players is 40.

It is already bot enabled

some of the weapons may be a bit close but you can work it out =). all weapons are equipped with 100 ammo so have fun fraggin !

This is my first map, I made it all myself with advice and ideas from Evil|Angus|UK and Vaatrad's tutorials, youTube 'vaatrad' to watch them, hint start with #1 and work your way up xD. The map is intended to be a short game, no longer than 2 minutes, and the other team isn't intended to cross the bridge.  They hide behind their brick walls and venture to their other areas. I haven't found any glitches so far but any recommendations are useful. There is work going on for an extra dimmension, the 'sewers' and basements etc. but i have other ideas and so it has been shunted to the back of the que.

This is my third CS : Source map, and it includes
 good graphics for an fy map and strategic spots 
for shootouts. The map contains a detailed cybercafe 
with breakable computers and file cabinets to save 
your head! The middle of the map contains the 
traditional "quad area" but in high graphical detail. 
I spent time on this map to ensure it was done right! 
The map supports 32 players yet 16 recommended for 
performance. Most of all have fun!
